cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the automatic construction of business taxonomies from corporate annual reports, which involves text processing and clustering techniques commonly used in information retrieval. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely category as the paper uses natural language processing techniques to extract concepts from the text. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are relevant categories as the paper proposes a new method for clustering concepts hierarchically, which involves machine learning and AI techniques. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a less likely category but still relevant as the paper deals with organizing and structuring information from corporate annual reports, which is a database management task.
